title: Xi Jinping looks back as aide blocked from BRICS venue

title: Putin Warns Poland â€˜Aggressionâ€™ Toward Belarus Is Attack on Russia
description: Russian President Vladimir Putin warned Poland that he would treat any â€œaggressionâ€ toward ally Belarus as an attack on his own country, following Warsawâ€™s decision to send troops to reinforce its eastern border in response to the presence of Wagner mercenary forces in its neighbor.â€œAggression against Belarus will mean aggression against the Russian Federation,â€ Putin said in televised comments during a Security Council Meeting Friday. â€œWe will respond to this with all the means at our disposal,â€ he said, referencing a long-established union state between Belarus and Russia.The threats, which could exacerbate tensions between Russia and Europe, arenâ€™t the first the Kremlin has leveled against Poland, which is one of Kyivâ€™s biggest supporters in the war with Russia. title: Macron 'Confident' France Will Beat Argentina in World Cup Final
description: President Emmanuel Macron on Thursday praised the French football team, after it defeated Morocco to reach the World Cup final in Qatar.France beat Morocco 2-0 to reach the World Cup final against Argentina, in a historic match between the defending champion and Africaâ€™s first ever semifinalist.When asked if he was scared of Argentina's captain Lionel Messi, Macron cheekily said he preferred the Paris Saint-Germain forward when he played in the French capital."He's a great player when he plays in Paris, but I prefer him in Paris than on his national team," the French president said with a smile.Macron added that the French had a lot of "respect" for their final adversary but that he believed his Les Bleus were "well prepared"."I am very confident in this chemistry and I think this is a team with a lot of willingness, generosity and it will have 68 million people backing them," he said.Subscribe to our YouTube channel: https://bit.ly/2TwO8GmSubscribe to our newest channel Quicktake Explained: https://bit.ly/3iERrupBloomberg Quicktake brings you live global news and original shows spanning business, technology, politics and culture. title: Putin Says LGBTQ Community Is Part of Russian Society
description: Russian President Vladimir Putin said the LGBTQ community is part of society while Russian authorities asked the Supreme Court to declare the LGBTQ 'movement' extremist.Speaking at the cultural forum in St. Petersburg on Friday, Putin said it's required to show the life of the LGBTQ community when competing at cultural contests in Western countries, but added that they have the right to do so."This is also part of society, this is what people live for. It's only bad if they are the only ones to win the competition," Putin said.On the same day, the Russian Justice Ministry said it has filed a lawsuit with the nation's Supreme Court to outlaw the LGBTQ+ â€œinternational public movementâ€ as extremist, the latest crippling blow against the already beleaguered LGBTQ+ community in the increasingly conservative country.The ministry said in an online statement announcing the lawsuit that authorities have identified â€œsigns and manifestations of extremist natureâ€ in â€œthe activities of the LGBT movement active" in Russia, including â€œincitement of social and religious discord.â€Russia's Supreme Court has scheduled a hearing to consider the lawsuit for Nov. 30, the ministry said.It is not yet clear what exactly the label would entail for LGBTQ+ people in Russia if the Supreme Court sides with the Justice Ministry, and the ministry did not immediately respond to a request for comment.But the move in itself represents the latest, and possibly by far the most drastic, step in the decade-long crackdown on gay rights in Russia unleashed under President Vladimir Putin, who has put â€œtraditional family valuesâ€ at the cornerstone of his rule.--------Subscribe to our YouTube channel: https://bit.ly/2TwO8GmSubscribe to Bloomberg Originals: https://www.youtube.com/BloombergTVBloomberg Quicktake brings you global social video spanning business, technology, politics and culture. lt was not clear what horizon if the visible universe really meant.

Horizon is not the curvature of space (as standing in a beach model would entitle), but the speed in which the expansion takes place at the "edge" of what's visible in our 3D spherical universe buble.

At those speeds light "dilutes" to the point of being currently undetectable, and that's the edge for our current instruments.

The "dilution" of the visible light is the horizon, nothing more.

And the speed of expansion makes whatever may be beyond that point invisible to us.

We may live in an infinite universe afterall.

I used to do percussive dance & these two dudes kept showing up everywhere I went. Turned out they were not axe murderers stalking me, but headhunters for a festival overseas. So I end up on The Jerry Anderson Show (British version of Johnny Carson). Sudden National fame in whatever country you've gone off to is surreal, isn't it? I wish I would have seen your videos, or worked around Russell Crowe before going over. I was 24, but so much like a little kid, gallumping around, taking it all in - completely oblivious to how extraordinary this all was. And because it was me - my ordinary life - I realize now, on some level, I was dismissive of how big this all was (not just as "fame," but until I was old enough to be embarrassed for myself, the gratitude. I was never stuck up, but I allowed myself to be rushed instead of generous with my ability to make moments for people.
I no longer perform but when I did, and I did that, it was always like prayer, the person's joy multiplying in my heart. Then, I see you do this with a whole audience - and Arnold. Yeah, next level. You teach Truths with your lifethrill every time I watch.
I gotta check your tour dates, go for a drive to laugh -- and to thank you.

title: Kim Jong-un's new year message
description: The North Korean leader, Kim Jong-un, has said his resolve for complete denuclearisation remains unchanged but he may have to seek a 'new path' if the United States continues to demand one-sided disarmament by his regime. In his new year address, Kim said there would be faster progress on denuclearisation if the United States took corresponding action. He added that he is willing to meet Donald Trump at any time to produce results that the international community would welcome.
